" src="https://i.imgur.com/hjNa6Hv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-news/jimmy-carter-u-s-is-an-oligarchy-with-unlimited-political-bribery-63262/

Yes. This article is 7 years old. But I read it today when thinking of how the US and NATO are turning Russian oligarchs against Putin.

Immediately it made me think "why couldn't Putin do it right back to us, but using cyber security and social warfare instead of sanctions?"

Russia isn't done making trouble!

TLDR WARNING: Following could confuse/bore anyone.

-------

Part 1 - He will go after our oligarchs

Putin is quickly losing political propaganda control within his country. Although it takes a lot for Russian people to revolt, he will try to compensate and avoid losing support. Right now his support is fairly high internally but it's going to fall soon. Russian mothers alone are going to get sick of this shit. 

His best way to stay in power without really barbaric dictatorship crap on his own people? I think he is likely to try and confuse the issue by disinformation inside Russia and (worse) cyber warfare outside of Russia.

He can't cut off US oligarchy financially. But he can use cyber security and warfare to make a mess of credit, power grids and internet spaces. I think he will likely try this front. They could lose billions.

Especially on the heels of the pandemic, markets aren't so hot in the first place.

-------

Part 2 - He will use disinformation & more to further divide western people's unity

He can take advantage of the huge class hatred in the US to divide our country. He is, after all, from a counter intelligence background. But even more than that, he might drive social and culture warfare up even more.

He already divided at least the US population a huge amount up to and after the 2016 election. So he's had practice and we Americans are easily angered right now between political, racial, theist/atheist and class divisions.

Someone's got to say it ... the problem isn't just the western oligarchs. It's the unity of western people which is a mess right now. He can exploit how un-unified the people of the west are right now. US - race. UK - Brexit. Canada - Trudeau. Etc etc etc. There's a little weak spot for each country and alliance.

He didn't think Ukraine would pull together and fight back. He's lost that gambit. But the chess game isn't over!!!

This is about to get very very confusing and uglier globally. And I don't mean fuckin nukes!! Social shit is about to get real. He's going to unleash even more emotional weapons like fear, mistrust and existential dread.

Thoughts on how we can thwart Putin if he tries further division? 

Is it possible to unify the west but keep our personal intellectual and other distinctions & disagreements intact without breaking down thru anger and mistrust?

Or is this going to get stuck in user sub and I'll get like 2 useful thoughtful comments? Lol.

-------

Post FrontPage Edit:

Well, this DIDN'T get stuck in user-sub! THANK YOU to everyone who upvoted plus especially those who commented your opinions.

Also, big fat THANK YOU to those who gave me Accolade Awards. I have had posts with higher points but never had SIX AWARDS. My ego is huge now. :-) 

I want to re-post & re-ask the question at the end of my rambling TLDR text if anyone is interested. I didn't get very many direct answers to the question:

"Is it possible to unify the west but keep our personal intellectual and other distinctions & disagreements intact without breaking down thru anger and mistrust?"

To clarify, I'm summarizing the background to re-ask the question:
1. Individuals sometimes get divided when we discuss ideas.
2. People can/often stop debating the merits of an idea due to emotional defensiveness.
3. In the US, the general population (GP) always has disagreements & some emotional defensiveness to ideas but maintains overall unification by a very firm belief in its destiny for ideological freedom.
4. Putin/Russia encouraged division in the US GP in 2016 by cyber internet disinformation & emotional "warfare" by posts, fake accounts, twisting facts or arguments, etc..
5. The division has damaged belief in ideological freedom balanced with unity.
6. Putin may (will) try to divide the US and world GP further in 2022 by more ideological division. This supports his invasion & future plans by dividing his enemies internally.

